main event: A single unidentified flying object was observed by civilian witnesses in Tallahassee, Florida on February 3, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as a round, greyish-purple object the size of a grapefruit, with good depth and a phosphorus glow.
The object was observed making a rapid east-to-west flight path, emitting a humming sound.
The sighting was also reported by the pilot of an Eastern Airlines flight and the tower operator at Jacksonville.
Despite numerous witnesses, including 12-15 people who called the local radio station and 20-25 who called the local newspaper, the investigation was inconclusive.

The investigating officer noted that the lack of physical evidence and the involvement of mainly college students or adults affiliated with the university lent an impression that the sighting may have been a hoax, though the interviews conducted by a newspaper reporter suggested the sightings were credible.
sighted object: single round, greyish-purple object with phosphorus glow
witnesses: civilian witnesses, Eastern Airlines pilot, Jacksonville tower operator
